    "narrative": "The LawDog offensive unit for 2026-04-08 is headlined by **Tyler Freeman**, who enters the day with our highest efficiency rating at 71.80. This surge is driven by a favorable matchup against a vulnerable starter, combined with a 14% park-factor boost that elevates his raw projection. **Bryson Stott** (68.43) and **Lawrence Butler** (65.37) round out the top of our board; **Bryson Stott** benefits significantly from a 13% platoon edge against a right-handed arm, while **Lawrence Butler** is poised to exploit a positive park factor and a solid matchup. Conversely, we are mitigating risk against elite arms like Ragans and Ohtani, which suppressed the scores for **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (55.84) and **Daulton Varsho** (52.66), though their roles in the order keep them active for their potential to provide category-wide impact.\n\nThe most difficult decision on today\u2019s bench was **Matt Chapman**, who fell just short of the cut with a 53.41 score. While his platoon advantage against Nola is favorable, the combination of a negative park factor and the presence of an elite catcher behind the plate created too much friction to justify a start over the higher-upside efficiency of our middle infielders. Looking at the broader slate, we must remain cautious of the volatility introduced by elite opposing pitching. While **Gleyber Torres** holds a serviceable 55.61, the 13% drag from his platoon disadvantage requires close monitoring, despite the boost provided by favorable wind conditions. We are prioritizing players who maximize contact and stolen base potential today, as we look to capitalize on the specific matchups that favor our roster\u2019s speed and situational strengths.",
